110 state may, in writing, request a hearing within
111 ten days of receipt of the court's notification
112 that the court intends to grant probation. Upon
113 the state's request for a hearing, the court
114 shall grant a hearing as soon as reasonably
115 possible. If the state does not respond to the
116 court's notice in writing within ten days, the
117 court may proceed upon its own motion to grant
118 probation.
